function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(word[1])), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` function to iterate over the input `words`. It checks if the first character of each word is uppercase using the `isuppercase` function and indexing the first character with `[1]`. The filtered words that start with a capital letter are returned.
